Q1: Work on the dj.csv index data which contains DJ index daily data.

    1. Subset your data to dates between 1985-01-01 and 2007-12-31.
    1. Construct a 7 day RSI for your DJ data
    1. How many days in total that the RSI is above or equal 70? How many days in total that the RSI is below or equal 30?
    1. Check the performance of the following strategy: Buy the dji index at the close price when the rsi rises from below the oversold line (line 30), sell it at the close price on the following day. That is buy the stock if yesterdays RSI < 30 but todays RSI >=30.
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'

## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
library(zoo)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
dj=read.csv("dj.csv")
dj$date = as.character(dj$date)
dj = dj %>% filter (date>='1985-01-01' &(date<='2007-12-31'))
dj = dj %>% mutate(delta=dji-lag(dji,1)) %>%
  mutate(up.val = ifelse(delta>=0,delta,0),
         down.val = ifelse(delta<0,-delta,0))
dj = dj[2:nrow(dj),]
dj = dj %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(up.first.avg=rollapply(up.val,width=7,align='right',fill=NA,
                                FUN=mean,na.rm=T),
         down.first.avg=rollapply(down.val,width=7,align='right',fill=NA,
                                FUN=mean,na.rm=T))
dj$up.avg = dj$up.first.avg
dj$down.avg = dj$down.first.avg

for (t in 8:length(dj$up.avg)){
  dj$up.avg[t] = dj$up.avg[t-1]*6/7 + dj$up.val[t]*1/7
  dj$down.avg[t] = dj$down.avg[t-1]*6/7 + dj$down.val[t]*1/7
}

dj$rs = dj$up.avg/dj$down.avg
dj$rsi = 100-100/(1+dj$rs)

cat("n days RSI>=70: ",length(which(dj$rsi>=70)),"\n")
## n days RSI>=70:  1168
cat("n days RSI<=30: ",length(which(dj$rsi<=30)))
## n days RSI<=30:  466
dj = dj %>% mutate(lag.rsi=lag(rsi,1)) %>%
  mutate(buy.flag=ifelse(((lag.rsi<30)&(rsi>=30)),1,0))
dj = dj %>% mutate(buy.flag=ifelse(is.na(buy.flag),0,buy.flag))
dj = dj %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  mutate(ret.lead=lead(dji,1)/dji-1) %>%
  mutate(ret.strat=ret.lead*buy.flag) %>%
  mutate(ret.cum=cumprod(ret.strat+1))
plot(dj$ret.cum~as.Date(dj$date),type='l',
     xlab='date',ylab='cummulative return')

Calculate your Equal-weighted index return over the entire periods, however, rather than reallocate monthly, reallocate your portfolio at the begining of each quarter, that is, the reallocation dates are the first trading date after 01-01, 04-01, 07-01, 10-01 each year. library(dplyr)

load("crsp.sample.RData")
crsp.ret = spread(crsp.sample[,c("permno","date","ret")],permno,ret)

crsp.ret = crsp.ret %>% 
  mutate(ret=ifelse(is.na(ret),0,ret))

crsp.ret$yysea = as.yearqtr(crsp.ret$date, format = "%Y-%m-%d")
crsp.ret = crsp.ret %>% group_by(permno,yysea) %>% 
  mutate(cumret=cumprod(ret+1))
crsp.ew = crsp.ret %>% group_by(date) %>% 
  summarise(ew=mean(cumret),
  yysea=first(yysea))
crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% filter(yysea!=first(yysea))

plot(crsp.ret.2012Q1$ew~crsp.ret.2012Q1$date,type='l')

crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% group_by(yysea) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(ret=ew/lag(ew,1)-1,
         ret=ifelse(is.na(ret),ew-1,ret)) %>% ungroup() %>%
  mutate(cumret=cumprod(ret+1))
plot(crsp.ew$cumret,type='l')

Q3: Work on data crsp.sample2.RData

  1. When is the first date that each stock start to have return data?
  2. Assume the first date you achieve from a. is the launch date(IPO date) of each stock, build your monthly reallocation equal-weighted portfolio index taking into account of launch date of a stock. For example, on 2011-01-04, if only 9 out of 10 stocks launched, your index should only contain 9 stocks weighted average rather than 10 stocks. Plot the cumulative return of your index in 2013-01 and 2011-01.
library(dplyr)
load("crsp.sample2.RData")
s2 = crsp.sample2 %>% group_by(permno) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  summarise(first.date=first(date))
print(s2)

crsp.ew = crsp.sample2 %>% select(permno,date,ret)
crsp.ew = spread(crsp.ew,permno,ret)
crsp.ew = gather(crsp.ew,permno,ret,-date)
crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% group_by(permno) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(ipo=date[which(!is.na(ret))[1]]) %>% ungroup()
crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% filter(date>=ipo) %>% arrange(permno,date)
crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% mutate(yymm=substr(date,1,7)) %>%
  group_by(permno,yymm) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(cumret=cumprod(ret+1)) %>% ungroup()
crsp.ew = crsp.ew %>% group_by(date) %>% 
  summarise(ew=mean(cumret),
            yymm=first(yymm)) %>% ungroup()
crsp.ew.201301 = crsp.ew %>% filter(yymm=='2013-01')
plot(crsp.ew.201301$ew,type='l')

crsp.ew.201101 = crsp.ew %>% filter(yymm=='2011-01')
plot(crsp.ew.201101$ew,type='l')
